## 2. Fenêtre de Perte d'Event : Transactional Outbox

### Le Problème

```java
@Transactional
public void process(String reviewId, String memberId) {
    status.setStatus(ProcessStatus.SUCCESS);
    statusRepo.save(status);
    // COMMIT HAPPENS HERE
    
    // ⚠️ Container crash ici = event perdu à jamais
    events.publishEvent(new MemberProcessingAttemptFinished(reviewId));
}
```

### Solution : Outbox Pattern

L'event est persisté DANS la même transaction que le changement d'état. Un poller séparé lit l'outbox et publie les events.

#### Step 1 : Outbox Entity

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = "EVENT_OUTBOX")
public class OutboxEvent {
    
    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.UUID)
    private String id;
    
    @Column(nullable = false)
    private String aggregateType; // "MemberProcessStatus"
    
    @Column(nullable = false)
    private String aggregateId;   // reviewId
    
    @Column(nullable = false)
    private String eventType;     // "MemberProcessingAttemptFinished"
    
    @Column(columnDefinition = "CLOB")
    private String payload;       // JSON
    
    @Column(nullable = false)
    private Instant createdAt;
    
    @Column(nullable = false)
    private OutboxStatus status;  // PENDING, PUBLISHED, FAILED
    
    private Instant publishedAt;
}

public enum OutboxStatus {
    PENDING, PUBLISHED, FAILED
}
```

#### Step 2 : Écriture dans l'Outbox (même transaction)

```java
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class BlockAsyncWorker {

    private final OutboxRepository outboxRepo;
    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;

    @Async("workerExecutor")
    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void process(String reviewId, String memberId) {
        var status = statusRepo.findByKey(reviewId, memberId);
        
        try {
            status.setStatus(ProcessStatus.PROCESSING);
            statusRepo.save(status);

            var data = externalClient.fetch(memberId);
            blockService.createBlocks(data, reviewId);

            status.setStatus(ProcessStatus.SUCCESS);
            
        } catch (Exception e) {
            status.setStatus(ProcessStatus.ERROR);
            status.setErrorMessage(truncate(e.getMessage(), 500));
        }
        
        statusRepo.save(status);
        
        // Écriture Outbox dans la MÊME transaction
        var event = new MemberProcessingAttemptFinished(reviewId, memberId, status.getStatus());
        outboxRepo.save(OutboxEvent.builder()
            .aggregateType("MemberProcessStatus")
            .aggregateId(reviewId)
            .eventType(event.getClass().getSimpleName())
            .payload(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(event))
            .status(OutboxStatus.PENDING)
            .createdAt(Instant.now())
            .build()
        );
        
        // COMMIT : status ET outbox event sont persistés ensemble
    }
}
```

#### Step 3 : Outbox Poller

```java
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Slf4j
public class OutboxPoller {

    private final OutboxRepository outboxRepo;
    private final ApplicationEventPublisher eventPublisher;
    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;
    
    // Map eventType -> Class pour désérialisation
    private static final Map<String, Class<?>> EVENT_TYPES = Map.of(
        "MemberProcessingAttemptFinished", MemberProcessingAttemptFinished.class
    );

    @Scheduled(fixedDelay = 100) // Poll toutes les 100ms
    @Transactional
    public void pollAndPublish() {
        // Récupère un batch d'events pending avec lock
        var events = outboxRepo.findPendingWithLock(50);
        
        for (var outbox : events) {
            try {
                Class<?> eventClass = EVENT_TYPES.get(outbox.getEventType());
                Object event = objectMapper.readValue(outbox.getPayload(), eventClass);
                
                eventPublisher.publishEvent(event);
                
                outbox.setStatus(OutboxStatus.PUBLISHED);
                outbox.setPublishedAt(Instant.now());
                
            } catch (Exception e) {
                log.error("Failed to publish event {}", outbox.getId(), e);
                outbox.setStatus(OutboxStatus.FAILED);
            }
            outboxRepo.save(outbox);
        }
    }
}
```

```java
@Repository
public interface OutboxRepository extends JpaRepository<OutboxEvent, String> {
    
    @Lock(LockModeType.PESSIMISTIC_WRITE)
    @Query("""
        SELECT e FROM OutboxEvent e 
        WHERE e.status = 'PENDING' 
        ORDER BY e.createdAt ASC
        """)
    List<OutboxEvent> findPendingWithLock(Pageable pageable);
    
    default List<OutboxEvent> findPendingWithLock(int limit) {
        return findPendingWithLock(PageRequest.of(0, limit));
    }
}
```

#### Step 4 : Cleanup Job

```java
@Scheduled(cron = "0 0 2 * * *") // Tous les jours à 2h
@Transactional
public void cleanupOldEvents() {
    var threshold = Instant.now().minus(Duration.ofDays(7));
    outboxRepo.deleteByStatusAndPublishedAtBefore(OutboxStatus.PUBLISHED, threshold);
}
```

### Garanties

| Scénario | Comportement |
|----------|--------------|
| Crash après commit | Event est dans Outbox → Poller le publie au restart |
| Crash avant commit | Transaction rollback → Rien n'est persisté → Cohérent |
| Double publish | Possible si crash après publish mais avant update status → Le listener doit être **idempotent** |

