## 3. Recovery des PROCESSING "Stuck"

### Le Problème

Un worker commence, met le status à `PROCESSING`, puis le pod crash. Le row reste `PROCESSING` indéfiniment.

### Solution : Heartbeat + Recovery

#### Option A : Timeout-based (Simple)

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = "MEMBER_PROCESS_STATUS")
public class MemberProcessStatus {
    // ... existing fields
    
    private Instant processingStartedAt; // Nouveau champ
}
```

```java
// Dans le worker, au début du processing
status.setStatus(ProcessStatus.PROCESSING);
status.setProcessingStartedAt(Instant.now());
statusRepo.save(status);
```

```java
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Slf4j
public class StuckProcessingRecovery {

    private static final Duration STUCK_THRESHOLD = Duration.ofMinutes(10);
    private static final int MAX_INDIVIDUAL_RETRIES = 3;

    @Scheduled(fixedRate = 60_000) // Toutes les minutes
    @Transactional
    public void recoverStuckProcessing() {
        var threshold = Instant.now().minus(STUCK_THRESHOLD);
        
        var stuckRows = statusRepo.findStuckProcessing(threshold);
        
        if (stuckRows.isEmpty()) {
            return;
        }
        
        log.warn("Found {} stuck PROCESSING rows", stuckRows.size());
        
        // Group by reviewId pour re-dispatcher en batch
        Map<String, List<MemberProcessStatus>> byReview = stuckRows.stream()
            .collect(Collectors.groupingBy(MemberProcessStatus::getReviewId));
        
        for (var entry : byReview.entrySet()) {
            String reviewId = entry.getKey();
            List<MemberProcessStatus> stuck = entry.getValue();
            
            for (var status : stuck) {
                if (status.getRetryCount() >= MAX_INDIVIDUAL_RETRIES) {
                    // Trop de retries → marquer en erreur définitive
                    status.setStatus(ProcessStatus.ERROR);
                    status.setErrorMessage("Max retries exceeded (stuck recovery)");
                    log.error("Member {} exceeded max retries", status.getMemberId());
                } else {
                    // Reset pour retry
                    status.setStatus(ProcessStatus.TO_DO);
                    status.setRetryCount(status.getRetryCount() + 1);
                    status.setProcessingStartedAt(null);
                }
                statusRepo.save(status);
            }
            
            // Re-trigger le dispatch pour ce review
            blockOrchestrator.dispatchPending(reviewId);
        }
    }
}
```

```java
@Repository
public interface ProcessStatusRepository extends JpaRepository<MemberProcessStatus, String> {
    
    @Query("""
        SELECT s FROM MemberProcessStatus s 
        WHERE s.status = 'PROCESSING' 
        AND s.processingStartedAt < :threshold
        """)
    List<MemberProcessStatus> findStuckProcessing(@Param("threshold") Instant threshold);
}
```

#### Option B : Heartbeat (Pour processing très long)

Si certains processing peuvent légitimement durer plus de 10 minutes :

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = "MEMBER_PROCESS_STATUS")
public class MemberProcessStatus {
    // ... existing fields
    
    private Instant lastHeartbeat;
}
```

```java
@Service
public class BlockAsyncWorker {

    @Async("workerExecutor")
    public void process(String reviewId, String memberId) {
        var status = statusRepo.findByKey(reviewId, memberId);
        
        // Start heartbeat thread
        var heartbeatTask = scheduler.scheduleAtFixedRate(
            () -> updateHeartbeat(reviewId, memberId),
            0, 30, TimeUnit.SECONDS
        );
        
        try {
            // ... processing logic
        } finally {
            heartbeatTask.cancel(false);
        }
    }
    
    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void updateHeartbeat(String reviewId, String memberId) {
        statusRepo.updateHeartbeat(reviewId, memberId, Instant.now());
    }
}
```

Le recovery check `lastHeartbeat` au lieu de `processingStartedAt`.

**Ma recommandation** : Option A (timeout simple) suffit pour ton use case. 10 minutes est généreux pour un call API + création de blocks.

