## 4. Idempotence du Dispatch

### Le Problème

```java
public void dispatchPending(String reviewId) {
    var pending = statusRepo.findPending(reviewId);
    pending.forEach(p -> asyncWorker.process(reviewId, p.getMemberId()));
}
```

Si appelé deux fois rapidement → le même member est dispatché deux fois → processing dupliqué.

### Solution : Claim Pattern

```java
@Repository
public interface ProcessStatusRepository extends JpaRepository<MemberProcessStatus, String> {
    
    /**
     * Tente de "claim" un member pour processing.
     * Retourne 1 si claim réussi, 0 si déjà pris.
     */
    @Modifying
    @Query("""
        UPDATE MemberProcessStatus s 
        SET s.status = 'PROCESSING', s.processingStartedAt = :now 
        WHERE s.reviewId = :reviewId 
        AND s.memberId = :memberId 
        AND s.status IN ('TO_DO', 'ERROR')
        """)
    int claimForProcessing(
        @Param("reviewId") String reviewId,
        @Param("memberId") String memberId,
        @Param("now") Instant now
    );
}
```

```java
@Service
public class BlockAsyncWorker {

    @Async("workerExecutor")
    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void process(String reviewId, String memberId) {
        
        // Tente de claim - si déjà PROCESSING, on skip
        int claimed = statusRepo.claimForProcessing(reviewId, memberId, Instant.now());
        
        if (claimed == 0) {
            log.debug("Member {} already being processed, skipping", memberId);
            return; // Pas d'event publié - le "vrai" worker le fera
        }
        
        var status = statusRepo.findByKey(reviewId, memberId);
        
        try {
            var data = externalClient.fetch(memberId);
            blockService.createBlocks(data, reviewId);
            status.setStatus(ProcessStatus.SUCCESS);
            
        } catch (Exception e) {
            status.setStatus(ProcessStatus.ERROR);
            status.setErrorMessage(e.getMessage());
        }
        
        statusRepo.save(status);
        
        // Outbox event...
    }
}
```

### Garantie

| Scénario | Comportement |
|----------|--------------|
| Double dispatch simultané | Premier thread claim → UPDATE returns 1. Second thread → UPDATE returns 0 → skip |
| Retry après ERROR | status = ERROR → claim réussit → re-processing |
| Recovery après stuck | status reset TO_DO → claim réussit |

