## 5. Salesforce Partial Batch Failure

### Le Problème

Tu envoies 200 items, SF en accepte 150, en rejette 50. Comment tu gères ?

### Solution : Granular SF Status Tracking

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = "SF_SYNC_STATUS")
public class SalesforceSyncStatus {
    
    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.UUID)
    private String id;
    
    private String reviewId;
    private String entityType;    // "MEMBER" ou "BLOCK"
    private String entityId;      // memberId ou blockId
    
    @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)
    private SyncStatus status;    // PENDING, SUCCESS, FAILED, SKIPPED
    
    private String salesforceId;  // ID retourné par SF si succès
    private String errorMessage;
    private int retryCount;
}

public enum SyncStatus {
    PENDING, SUCCESS, FAILED, SKIPPED
}
```

```java
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class SalesforceSync {

    private static final int BATCH_SIZE = 200;
    private static final int MAX_SYNC_RETRIES = 3;

    @Transactional
    public SyncBatchResult syncMemberBatch(String reviewId, int offset) {
        
        // 1. Récupère les membres SUCCESS, pas encore sync (ou FAILED avec retry < max)
        var toSync = syncStatusRepo.findPendingMembers(reviewId, BATCH_SIZE);
        
        if (toSync.isEmpty()) {
            return SyncBatchResult.empty();
        }
        
        // 2. Appel SF
        var sfRequest = toSync.stream()
            .map(this::mapToSalesforcePayload)
            .toList();
        
        SalesforceResponse response = salesforceClient.upsertBatch(sfRequest);
        
        // 3. Process résultats individuels
        int successCount = 0;
        int failedCount = 0;
        List<String> failedIds = new ArrayList<>();
        
        for (int i = 0; i < response.getResults().size(); i++) {
            var result = response.getResults().get(i);
            var syncStatus = toSync.get(i);
            
            if (result.isSuccess()) {
                syncStatus.setStatus(SyncStatus.SUCCESS);
                syncStatus.setSalesforceId(result.getId());
                successCount++;
            } else {
                syncStatus.setRetryCount(syncStatus.getRetryCount() + 1);
                
                if (syncStatus.getRetryCount() >= MAX_SYNC_RETRIES) {
                    syncStatus.setStatus(SyncStatus.FAILED);
                    syncStatus.setErrorMessage(result.getError());
                } else {
                    // Reste PENDING pour retry au prochain batch
                    syncStatus.setErrorMessage(result.getError());
                }
                
                failedCount++;
                failedIds.add(syncStatus.getEntityId());
            }
            
            syncStatusRepo.save(syncStatus);
        }
        
        return new SyncBatchResult(successCount, failedCount, failedIds);
    }
}
```

```java
public record SyncBatchResult(
    int successCount,
    int failedCount,
    List<String> failedIds
) {
    public static SyncBatchResult empty() {
        return new SyncBatchResult(0, 0, List.of());
    }
    
    public boolean hasMoreToSync() {
        return successCount > 0 || failedCount > 0;
    }
}
```

### Modification du Saga

```java
@ApplicationModuleListener
@Transactional
public void on(SyncBatchCompletedEvent event) {
    var saga = sagaRepo.findByIdForUpdate(event.reviewId());
    
    // On ne compte plus les offsets, on check ce qui reste à sync
    long pendingMembers = syncStatusRepo.countPending(event.reviewId(), "MEMBER");
    long pendingBlocks = syncStatusRepo.countPending(event.reviewId(), "BLOCK");
    
    if (pendingMembers > 0) {
        // Continue syncing members
        commandGateway.dispatch(new SyncMembersCommand(saga.getReviewId()));
    } else if (pendingBlocks > 0) {
        // Move to blocks
        commandGateway.dispatch(new SyncBlocksCommand(saga.getReviewId()));
    } else {
        // All done
        long failedTotal = syncStatusRepo.countFailed(event.reviewId());
        if (failedTotal > 0) {
            log.warn("Review {} completed with {} sync failures", event.reviewId(), failedTotal);
        }
        saga.setStep(SagaStep.FINALIZING);
    }
    
    sagaRepo.save(saga);
}
```

